    "body": "This PR implements a separate sharding scheme for calculating KV row addresses for SM100 forward, following the implementation in FA3. The load is broken into two stages now:\r\n\r\n1. Each of the load warp threads independently calculates a disjoint set of row addresses.\r\n2. A group of coalesced load threads accesses calculated addresses serially via shuffle sync.\r\n\r\nThis improves the memory bandwidth utilization when using irregular page sizes. Now hitting a peak of 5 TB/s and 1100+ TFLOPS for arbitrary page-size paged attention.\r\n\r\nOther optimizations:\r\n- Use thread0 head_dim indices for bound checking, known at compile-time\r\n- Increase register allocation for load warps\r\n- PR #1993 frees up 4 warps for loading when Q is small\r\n\r\n### Benchmark\r\n\r\nMemory Bound\r\n```\r\nBefore\r\npage_size,num_splits,batch_size,seqlen_q,seqlen_k,num_heads,num_heads_kv,head_dim,cache_size,dtype,avg_time_us,tflops,bw,correctness\r\n1,1,32,1,65536,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,1851.017261522388,18.56262449964431,2.3206113056272257,correct\r\n8,1,32,1,65536,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,1100.9392346828197,31.20947758565352,3.9016609170419203,correct\r\n32,1,32,1,65536,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,982.2988291198338,34.978905959592005,4.372896980696675,correct\r\n128,1,32,1,65536,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,815.8591217781454,42.11479341324734,5.264991797405021,correct\r\n\r\nAfter\r\npage_size,num_splits,batch_size,seqlen_q,seqlen_k,num_heads,num_heads_kv,head_dim,cache_size,dtype,avg_time_us,tflops,bw,correctness\r\n1,1,32,1,65536,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,770.9341534784623,44.56896638055083,5.571800866025589,correct\r\n8,1,32,1,65536,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,806.982965472903,42.57802188905528,5.322902425186613,correct\r\n32,1,32,1,65536,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,808.9174211201583,42.47620025344483,5.310173167060447,correct\r\n128,1,32,1,65536,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,818.9499721549074,41.955845333981806,5.245120862141616,correct\r\n```\r\n\r\nCompute Bound\r\n```\r\nBefore\r\npage_size,num_splits,batch_size,seqlen_q,seqlen_k,num_heads,num_heads_kv,head_dim,cache_size,dtype,avg_time_us,tflops,bw,correctness\r\n1,1,1,8192,8192,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,2602.1894129960897,422.53327996982836,0.0580261157185128,correct\r\n8,1,1,8192,8192,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,1790.1168914570114,614.2121964343266,0.08434920910505585,correct\r\n32,1,1,8192,8192,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,1733.3972011535673,634.3102590936921,0.08710925799321334,correct\r\n128,1,1,8192,8192,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,845.6515118670769,1300.1947165546203,0.17855457228075536,correct\r\n\r\nAfter\r\npage_size,num_splits,batch_size,seqlen_q,seqlen_k,num_heads,num_heads_kv,head_dim,cache_size,dtype,avg_time_us,tflops,bw,correctness\r\n1,1,1,8192,8192,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,938.4196730422192,1171.6630196077883,0.1609034298167434,correct\r\n8,1,1,8192,8192,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,932.6118282973766,1178.9595568215386,0.16190545671682507,correct\r\n32,1,1,8192,8192,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,903.7904841914371,1216.5558799389905,0.1670685259925982,correct\r\n128,1,1,8192,8192,32,4,128,524288,bfloat16,857.2937113770629,1282.537843430421,0.17612976975820602,correct\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Correctness\r\nThese changes continue to pass all tests under `test_flash_attn_kvcache`.\r\n\r\n```\r\n============================= test session starts ==============================\r\nplatform linux -- Python 3.12.1, pytest-9.0.2, pluggy-1.6.0\r\nrootdir: /root/flash_attn/tests\r\nconfigfile: pyproject.toml\r\ncollected 7208 items / 4136 deselected / 3072 selected\r\n\r\nflash_attn/tests/cute/test_flash_attn.py ............................... [  1%]\r\n........................................................................ [  3%]\r\n........................................................................ [  5%]\r\n........................................................................ [  8%]\r\n........................................................................ [ 10%]\r\n.......................